NumberWideningCrossesKinds
/ Regression anchor: integer and decimal numbers still widen across kinds in arithmetic —
/ 2 (int) + 3.5 (decimal) yields 5.5, the born-native number wrappers did not silo the kinds.
- set %a% = 2
- set %b% = 3.5
- add %a% and %b%, write to %sum%
- assert %sum% equals 5.5
